> He exits the Ark and stands atop the vessel, letting out a loud but non
> aggressive roar that he hoped would be heard by the others.  He gives three
> loud bellows, and then waits to hear its response.

OOC: I am not sure which others TUCSON is calling for. The dragons or
other Maximals.

<BIC>

TUCSON's roar echoed out over the landscape, like thunder it bounced
and echoed, is deep reverberous sound bouncing off mountain peaks and
valleys for miles.

Birds scatter into the air and animals flee as the sound startled them
into flight.

However there does not appear to be any other answer from anyone away
from the ARK.

However he does get a few calls closer to home . . .

"Was that you Tucson?" Came a call from LORD ELDER.

A call from LEO PRIME came in as well, "Tucson, was that your roar!"

WOLFGANG looked over at TUCSON and then continued on guard patrol.

(TAG)

- Preston
